OL,3,GOPINIONCCould red button provide a more
OL,4,Cinclusive TV experience for BSL viewers
OL,5,
OL,6,FSubtitles are, of course, easy to turn
OL,7,Foff and on. They aren't just used by
OL,8,Fpeople with profound hearing
OL,9,Fdifficulties. They are valued by some
OL,10,Fother viewers too. Perhaps a slight
OL,11,Fhearing difficulty makes it hard for
OL,12,Fthem to distinguish some speech? Or
OL,13,Fmaybe they just want to keep the sound
OL,14,Flow to avoid disturbing someone?
OL,16,FAudio description is a useful service
OL,17,Ffor those with poor eyesight and the
OL,18,Fblind.
OL,23,Uppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppp
